---
[v1] char: hw_random: mtk-rng: refactor driver to support SMC mode

Refactor the MediaTek TRNG driver to consolidate mtk-rng and mtk-rng-v2 into
a unified driver. The driver now supports both MMIO-based and SMC-based (Secure
Monitor Call) access methods. For SoCs where TF-A controls the RNG hardware
(MT7981/MT7986/MT7987/MT7988), the driver automatically uses SMC calls to obtain
random numbers. This eliminates the need for a separate mtk-rng-v2 driver and
provides a more flexible solution.
---
v1: Backport from openwrt-master commit to openwrt-25.12 branch after OpenWrt
    official 25.12 branch release.
